Description: Round-topped limestone stela with faded painted detail; only the winged sun-disc at the top and five lines of Hieroglyphic text are discernible.
Curator's comments: Young, T. 1828. Hieroglyphics, continued by the Royal Society of Literature; arranged by Thomas Young M.D.F.R.S. Vol. II, pl. 49. London. (facsimile of a better preserved text) PM III (2): 743 J. Quaegebeur, Chronique d'Egypte 49 (1974), 69 (no. 19).
